  "text": "There is some evidence that neoadjuvant chemotherapy may reduce hepatic micrometastasis and cancer recurrence. [CITATION_1] Wakai et al. in their study noted that neoadjuvant chemotherapy can reduce hepatic micrometastasis and cancer recurrence. [CITATION_2] However, their study was a retrospective, and a question remained unanswered that which patients derive benefit from neoadjuvant chemotherapy. To answer this question tumor characteristics and its correlation with hepatic micrometastasis should be considered.",
